HEADWORD: Hematinic
<hw>He`ma*tin"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Hematin</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Any substance, such as
an iron salt or organic compound containing iron, which when ingested
tends to increase the hemoglobin contents of the blood.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

